<|startoftext|>Headline:Trump says not considering resigning if Democrats refuse to fund healthcare bill (wtt.gov/2jBhZvxgY)
Content: "(Reuters) - U.S. Republican Donald Trump told reporters that he would not consider resigning if Democrats continue resisting a government funding bill he has vowed to kill, though he said: “If they’re going to do that, I probably would end up resigning.” Speaking at a news conference on Tuesday, Trump said he was unsure how many Democrats support the bill, which would fund the government through June until Feb. 10. But, he added: �They have no real idea what we would do. The (Obama) administration is having problems. We should be paying millions of dollars more for the things we’ve got to do that we’re doing.”   Trump told reporters that if Democrats failed to bring up the government’s debt limit or if they refused to fund it, he would consider doing it himself instead of using the budget as an excuse. The United States has budgeted the bills it must pass to fund its government for several months of 2017 at a cost of about $7 billion, and the United States must also fund that month’s bills through October. The bill includes a “continuing resolution” for military veterans who need medical care, a bill to help the struggling economy and a bill to keep the government open at some of the time when it runs out of money.   Obama will leave the White House on Thursday, leaving a $2 trillion in federal debt, and will spend about $8 billion on the government’s domestic social security program. On Monday, the White House put together a $500 million contingency fund set to be used for future military aid.  Trump also said the federal government might need to be even more generous over the next 10 days as funding is tight and Congress could pass the bill any time. “If this is going to be that important, I’ll probably need to get back out there faster,” he said. In a series of tweets late on Tuesday on Twitter, Trump said he was confident that there was enough support to fund government for the fiscal year. “Congress is working hard on healthcare, if they work. #Congresswork! I will be in quite a bit of pain if I go now, or if Congress stays in session for another three days!” he wrote.  Democrats have been working on their own “skinny budget (to fund government)” for months, but Trump is also considering using that as a bargaining chip in negotiations he is having with Trump.  ",<|endoftext|>
